SN  - 0020-6598
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.0020-6598.2004.00303.x
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - We introduce lack-of-recall of past transactions as an alternative assumption to anonymity in a model where trade is centralized. In environments where there is an intertemporal lack-of-double-coincidence of wants problem and lack-of-commitment, lack-of-recall can give rise to monetary equilibria that dominate nonmonetary outcomes in terms of welfare.
ER  - 

