T1  - SEQUENTIAL TWO-PLAYER GAMES WITH AMBIGUITY*
AU  - Eichberger, Jürgen
AU  - Kelsey, David
Y1  - 2004/11/01
PY  - 2004
DA  - 2004/11/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.0020-6598.2004.00304.x
T2  - International Economic Review
JF  - International Economic Review
JO  - International Economic Review
SP  - 1229
EP  - 1261
VL  - 45
IS  - 4
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0020-6598
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.0020-6598.2004.00304.x
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - If players' beliefs are strictly nonadditive, the Dempster?Shafer updating rule can be used to define beliefs off the equilibrium path. We define an equilibrium concept in sequential two-person games where players update their beliefs with the Dempster?Shafer updating rule. We show that in the limit as uncertainty tends to zero, our equilibrium approximates Bayesian Nash equilibrium. We argue that our equilibrium can be used to define a refinement of Bayesian Nash equilibrium by imposing context-dependent constraints on beliefs under uncertainty.
ER  - 

